### Relay Execute-Flow — multi-step HTTP pipeline via notx relay engine
### POST /v1/relay/execute-flow
###
### The flow engine:
###   1. Executes steps sequentially
###   2. After each step, applies "extract" rules to pull values from the
###      response into shared variables
###   3. Variables are available to all subsequent steps via {{varName}}
###   4. Returns all step results + the final variable state
###
### Supported extraction paths:
###   response.status              → HTTP status code as string
###   response.headers.<name>      → Response header value
###   response.body.<json_key>     → Top-level JSON field
###   response.body.<a>.<b>.<c>   → Nested JSON field (dot-separated)

### ── Example 1: Login + authenticated request ──────────────────────────────
### Step 1: POST /auth/token   → extract access_token
### Step 2: GET /profile       → use access_token in Authorization header

POST http://localhost:4060/v1/relay/execute-flow
Content-Type: application/json
X-Device-ID: notx:device:00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

{
  "variables": {
    "api_base": "https://httpbin.org",
    "username": "alice",
    "password": "s3cr3t"
  },
  "steps": [
    {
      "id": "login",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "url": "{{api_base}}/post",
        "headers": {
          "Content-Type": "application/json"
        },
        "body": "{\"username\":\"{{username}}\",\"password\":\"{{password}}\"}"
      },
      "extract": {
        "request_id": "response.body.json.username",
        "status_code": "response.status"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "fetch-data",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "url": "{{api_base}}/get",
        "headers": {
          "Accept": "application/json",
          "X-Logged-In-As": "{{request_id}}",
          "X-Prior-Status": "{{status_code}}"
        }
      },
      "extract": {
        "final_url": "response.body.url"
      }
    }
  ]
}

### ── Example 2: Sequential API calls with data threading ──────────────────
### Demonstrates extracting from nested JSON and threading values forward.

POST http://localhost:4060/v1/relay/execute-flow
Content-Type: application/json
X-Device-ID: notx:device:00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

{
  "variables": {
    "base_url": "https://httpbin.org"
  },
  "steps": [
    {
      "id": "step-1-get-headers",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "url": "{{base_url}}/headers",
        "headers": {
          "Accept": "application/json"
        }
      },
      "extract": {
        "host_header": "response.body.headers.Host",
        "response_status": "response.status"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "step-2-echo-back",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "url": "{{base_url}}/post",
        "headers": {
          "Content-Type": "application/json"
        },
        "body": "{\"original_host\":\"{{host_header}}\",\"step1_status\":\"{{response_status}}\"}"
      }
    }
  ]
}
